<source><![CDATA[client1:Actor "Client"
docker-core:Node "Docker Core"
docker-network:Node "Docker Network"
libnetwork:Node "libnetwork"
datastore-remote:Node[ep] "Datastore-remote"
datastore:Node "Datastore"
network-plugin:Node "Net Plugin"
ipam:Node "IPAM"

client1:docker-core.(docker run -net=foo xxx yyy)
docker-core:docker-core.createContainer()
docker-core[1]:docker-network.createEndpoint(container-id, "foo")
docker-network:endpoint-1=libnetwork.createEndpoint("foo")

docker-network:libnetwork.linkEndpoint(container-id, endpoint-1)
libnetwork:datastore.kv-put(EP-store, "foo", endpoint-set)

*1 libnetwork
endpoint-set is a set of all 
endpoints in a network.
This can be eventualy-consistent
*1

datastore:network-plugin.Endpoint Watch event

*1 network-plugin
** IPAM integration needs attention **
*1
network-plugin:datastore.kv-request("ipam", <subnet>)
datastore:ipam.IP Address request watch event
ipam:datastore.kv-cas("ipam",<subnet>,<ip>)
*1 network-plugin
cas (compare and swap) for
dist datastore consistency
*1

docker-core[0]:docker-core.startContainer()
[c: Asynchronous Datastore event on host2 for end-point creation in host1]

datastore-remote:datastore.New endpoint added to foo in host1
*1 datastore
This async event is realized only
on those hosts where there is an
active watch on network "foo"
*1



*2 datastore
endpoint-object is defined in the
net-plugin schema
*2
datastore:network-plugin.Endpoint watch event
*2 datastore
Plugin does its thing
to connect containers 
across hosts
*2

[/c]
